{{!
    @template mod_scormremote/errorpage

    This is a template is returned to the browser when something is wrong. It's mainly meant for displaying unauthorized access. For
    example when a client with no subscription access the page. Or when the seat limit has been reached.

    Classes required for JS:
    * none

    Data attributes required for JS:
    * none

    Context variables required for this template:
    * errorcode - can be anything but recommended use is a HTTP status code.
    * errortitle - the title of this page.
    * errormessage - the message with meaning full information, should contain information on how to resolve the error.

    Example context (json):
    {
        "errorcode": 403,
        "errortitle": "Unauthorised access",
        "errormessage": "We could not resolve the domain used to access this package. Please contact your teacher."
    }
}}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>{{errorcode}} {{errortitle}}</title>
    <style>
        html,
        body {
            margin: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
        }
        main {
            display: block;
            max-width: 74ch;
            margin: 0 auto 0 auto;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2em;
            margin: 0.67em 0;
            color: #888;
            font-weight: 300;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <main>
        <h1>{{errorcode}} | {{errortitle}}</h1>
        <p>{{errormessage}}</p>
    </main>
</body>
</html>